A 6-foot-tall granite monument of the Ten Commandments outside the Texas capitol building is constitutional, but smaller displays of the Decalogue inside two Kentucky county courthouses must go, the Supreme Court ruled in separate decisions Monday.
The Supreme Court ruled Monday that displaying the Ten Commandments on government property does not necessarily violate the constitutional principle that there must be a separation between church and state.
The US political, religious and  legal establishments are braced for two critical Supreme Court  rulings on the Ten Commandments, weighing heavily on the separation  of church and state.
